#: ../../source/docs/hardware/sensors/ultrasonics-hardware.rst:8
msgid ""
"Ultrasonic rangefinders are some of the most common rangefinders used in "
"FRC.  They are cheap, easy-to-use, and fairly reliable.  Ultrasonic "
"rangefinders work by emitting a pulse of high-frequency sound, and then "
"measuring how long it takes the echo to reach the sensor after bouncing "
"off the target.  From the measured time and the speed of sound in air, it"
" is possible to calculate the distance to the target."
msgstr ""

